274
00:14:38,384 --> 00:14:39,452
HE'S JUST NOT GETTING THE RESULTS

275
00:14:39,485 --> 00:14:41,487
HE SHOULD FOR SOMEONE SO BRIGHT.

276
00:14:41,521 --> 00:14:43,623
THREE DAYS LATE?

277
00:14:43,656 --> 00:14:45,925
THE FIRST I'VE HEARD OF IT. TOBY?

278
00:14:45,959 --> 00:14:48,261
JEFF? I'M TALKING TO YOU.

279
00:14:48,294 --> 00:14:50,663
THIS IS PARENTS' DAY. YOU'RE THE PARENT.

280
00:14:50,697 --> 00:14:52,365
WE'RE BOTH THE PARENTS HERE.

281
00:14:52,398 --> 00:14:54,601
AND WE'LL DISCUSS IT LATER, OKAY?

282
00:14:54,634 --> 00:14:56,202
WE WILL DISCUSS IT NOW.

283
00:14:56,236 --> 00:14:59,005
WHY AREN'T YOU HELPING TOBY GET HIS WORK IN ON TIME?

284
00:14:59,038 --> 00:15:01,207
WHY IS HE UNDER-ACHIEVING?

285
00:15:03,076 --> 00:15:05,144
TOBY AND I WILL WORK IT OUT.

286
00:15:05,178 --> 00:15:08,514
THANKS FOR BRINGING IT TO OUR ATTENTION.

287
00:15:13,653 --> 00:15:18,591
I'M SO PROUD OF YOU. RAVE REVIEW AFTER RAVE REVIEW.

288
00:15:19,359 --> 00:15:21,427
MOM, MY EDITORIAL!

289
00:15:22,562 --> 00:15:25,331
SO WHAT, YOU HAVE TO WATCH THIS VIDEO EVERY MORNING?

290
00:15:25,365 --> 00:15:27,533
A FREE COMPUTER IS A FREE COMPUTER, MAN.

291
00:15:27,567 --> 00:15:28,568
WHAT IDIOT WROTE THIS?

292
00:15:28,601 --> 00:15:31,604
EXCUSE ME? I WROTE THAT.

293
00:15:31,638 --> 00:15:33,373
OH, SORRY, I WAS -

294
00:15:33,406 --> 00:15:35,608
DON'T LOOK AT HER. IT'S MY PIECE AND I'M RIGHT.

295
00:15:35,642 --> 00:15:37,677
STUDENTS SHOULDN'T BE FORCE FED ADVERTISING

296
00:15:37,710 --> 00:15:39,679
WHEN WE'RE AT SCHOOL.

297
00:15:39,712 --> 00:15:41,648
IF YOU DON'T GET IT, YOU'RE THE IDIOT.

298
00:15:41,681 --> 00:15:43,316
EMMA...

299
00:15:43,349 --> 00:15:45,118
LOOK, IT'S NOT THAT SERIOUS.

300
00:15:45,151 --> 00:15:48,054
WHAT!? EXPRESSING MY OPINION ISN'T IMPORTANT?

301
00:15:48,087 --> 00:15:49,589
THAT'S ALL MY BROTHER IS TRYING TO DO.

302
00:15:49,622 --> 00:15:51,658
I COULD TELL. AND HE'S WRONG!

303
00:15:51,691 --> 00:15:56,062
I'M WRONG? TELL ME, IS IT FAIR OR IS IT WRONG

304
00:15:56,095 --> 00:15:58,131
THAT SEAN HERE HAS FALLEN BEHIND IN SCHOOL

305
00:15:58,164 --> 00:16:01,100
BECAUSE WE CAN'T AFFORD A COMPUTER.

306
00:16:01,801 --> 00:16:03,670
HE CAN DO HIS HOMEWORK HERE.

307
00:16:03,703 --> 00:16:05,638
WHAT, YEAH, ON THE FREE COMPUTERS HUH?

308
00:16:05,672 --> 00:16:08,141
IF YOU READ THE ENTIRE ARTICLE, YOU WOULD KNOW THAT-

309
00:16:08,174 --> 00:16:09,075
THAT IT'S A PIECE OF GARBAGE.

310
00:16:09,108 --> 00:16:11,177
IT IS NOT GARBAGE!

311
00:16:13,813 --> 00:16:18,751
IT LOOKS LIKE GARBAGE TO ME. IT SMELLS LIKE GARBAGE.

312
00:16:19,619 --> 00:16:21,654
ALL I'M TRYING TO SAY IS THERE'S TWO SIDES

313
00:16:21,688 --> 00:16:23,323
TO EVERY STORY.

314
00:16:23,356 --> 00:16:25,758
TRY TO REMEMBER THAT NEXT TIME.

315
00:16:33,733 --> 00:16:37,203
IT WAS ONLY ONCE. BUT STILL,

316
00:16:37,236 --> 00:16:41,074
SKIPPING A CLASS EVEN ONCE AT THIS GRADE LEVEL -

317
00:16:41,107 --> 00:16:43,242
WHAT IS GOING ON HERE?!

318
00:16:43,276 --> 00:16:46,446
ONE CLASS. I GOT CARRIED AWAY IN THE COMPUTER LAB.

319
00:16:46,479 --> 00:16:48,348
I THOUGHT MOVING IN WITH YOU AND JUNE CLEAVER

320
00:16:48,381 --> 00:16:50,383
WAS SUPPOSED TO BE GOOD FOR TOBY'S GRADES.

321
00:16:50,416 --> 00:16:51,551
WASN'T THAT THE POINT?

322
00:16:51,584 --> 00:16:52,151
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

323
00:16:52,185 --> 00:16:53,720
DAD, COME ON.

324
00:16:53,753 --> 00:16:55,154
I'M SAYING MAYBE WE NEED TO REASSESS

325
00:16:55,188 --> 00:16:57,690
TOBY'S LIVING ARRANGEMENTS.

326
00:16:57,724 --> 00:16:59,325
DON'T THREATEN ME.

327
00:16:59,359 --> 00:17:00,760
HEY, THAT'S YOUR GAME.

328
00:17:00,793 --> 00:17:03,262
WHAT? AND BREAKING COMMITMENTS IS YOURS?

329
00:17:03,296 --> 00:17:05,098
THAT'S WHY TOBY LIVES WITH ME.

330
00:17:05,131 --> 00:17:06,466
MR. AND MRS. ISAACS,

331
00:17:06,499 --> 00:17:08,434
THESE ARE COMMON PROBLEMS FOR MANY STUDENTS.

332
00:17:08,468 --> 00:17:09,702
SO IT'S MY FAULT?

333
00:17:09,736 --> 00:17:12,672
JEFF, LET'S NOT EVEN GET INTO THE REASONS WHY I LEFT, OKAY?

334
00:17:12,705 --> 00:17:16,409
REASONS WHY YOU LEFT? THERE'S ONLY ONE REASON, ANNE MARIE.

335
00:17:16,442 --> 00:17:19,712
YOUR CAREER. YOUR CAREER THAT MEANT SO MUCH MORE TO YOU

336
00:17:19,746 --> 00:17:20,780
THAN WE EVER DID.

337
00:17:20,813 --> 00:17:23,449
THAT'S WHY TOBY LIVES WITH ME AND HE'LL NEVER -

338
00:17:23,483 --> 00:17:26,519
MOM! DAD! YEAH, MY ASSIGNMENT WAS LATE!

339
00:17:26,552 --> 00:17:28,688
WHO'S TO BLAME? VIDEO GAMES.

340
00:17:28,721 --> 00:17:31,491
I'M TELLING YOU, THEY'RE DESTROYING MY GENERATION!

341
00:17:31,524 --> 00:17:32,658
TOBY, THIS ISN'T A JOKE.

342
00:17:32,692 --> 00:17:36,796
I'M NOT JOKING, OKAY? I DON'T HAVE AN EXCUSE.

343
00:17:36,829 --> 00:17:38,431
BUT DAD CAN'T DO MY HOMEWORK FOR ME

344
00:17:38,464 --> 00:17:40,666
OR MAKE SURE I GO TO CLASS.

345
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:43,836
IT'S MY LIFE, RIGHT? SO IT'S MY PROBLEM.

346
00:17:44,737 --> 00:17:46,572
STOP BLAMING EACH OTHER

347
00:17:46,606 --> 00:17:49,876
AND THEN USING ME AS ANOTHER EXCUSE TO ARGUE.

348
00:17:49,909 --> 00:17:54,280
BECAUSE IT'S NOT FAIR! I'LL TRY HARDER. I PROMISE.

349
00:17:58,851 --> 00:18:02,221
MOVING ON? ALRIGHT THEN,

350
00:18:02,789 --> 00:18:08,127
LET'S TAKE A LOOK AT SOME OF THE RECENT TEST RESULTS.

351
00:18:12,698 --> 00:18:15,268
OH HEY, HOW DID IT GO IN THERE?

352
00:18:15,301 --> 00:18:17,904
OH, AH, IT WENT AH, OKAY.

353
00:18:17,937 --> 00:18:19,739
TOBY JUST HAS TO APPLY HIMSELF MORE.

354
00:18:19,772 --> 00:18:20,840
YEAH, WE'RE GOING TO MAKE SURE

355
00:18:20,873 --> 00:18:24,210
THAT HE DOES HIS HOMEWORK ON TIME. BUT IT WENT OKAY.

356
00:18:24,243 --> 00:18:27,313
TOBY, HON, THAT'S SO - GREAT.

357
00:18:29,615 --> 00:18:31,784
HONEY LISTEN, I GOTTA RUN.

358
00:18:32,485 --> 00:18:33,753
GOTTA GET BACK TO WORK HUH?

359
00:18:33,786 --> 00:18:36,389
YEAH. BUT HEY, LISTEN.

360
00:18:36,856 --> 00:18:39,659
YOUR MESSAGE CAME IN LOUD AND CLEAR BACK THERE.

361
00:18:39,692 --> 00:18:41,627
TOBY, I'M REALLY SORRY.

362
00:18:42,895 --> 00:18:47,533
ALL THE STUFF BETWEEN YOUR DAD AND ME, IT'S TOUGH.

363
00:18:47,567 --> 00:18:48,768
I KNOW.

364
00:18:48,801 --> 00:18:51,604
HEY, I LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

365
00:18:52,338 --> 00:18:56,909
ASHLEY, YOU HAVE MY PERMISSION TO KEEP THIS MONKEY INLINE.

366
00:18:56,943 --> 00:18:59,212
OH I WILL DON'T YOU WORRY.

367
00:18:59,245 --> 00:19:00,313
AND IT WAS A PLEASURE TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

368
00:19:00,346 --> 00:19:03,249
AN ABSOLUTE JOY. BY THE WAY AH-

369
00:19:03,282 --> 00:19:06,886
I HAVE SOMETHING TO REMEMBER ME BY.

370
00:19:17,396 --> 00:19:18,798
IF YOU'RE INTERESTED IN ACTING, GIVE ME A CALL

371
00:19:18,831 --> 00:19:22,768
YOU HAVE AN INTERESTING LOOK.

372
00:20:04,610 --> 00:20:06,546
